  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large skillet, sauté the onion and bell pepper until tender.",
    "Add the garlic, diced tomatoes, black beans, and reviving spice blend. Cook for 2-3 minutes.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine the cooked rice, tamale filling, and sautéed vegetable mixture.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Top with shredded cheese and cover with aluminum foil.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 5-10 minutes.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
